!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

continuous /kənˈtɪnjʊəs/

1. ADJ A continuous process or event continues for a period of time without stopping. 持续的 (过程、事件) 

例： Residents report that they heard continuous gunfire. 居民们说他们听到了持续的枪声。 

2. continuously ADV 持续地 

例： The civil war has raged almost continuously since 

1976. 自1976年以来，激烈的内战几乎持续不断。 

3. ADJ A continuous line or surface has no gaps or holes in it. 连续的 (线条或平面) 

例： ...a continuous line of boats. …络绎不绝的船只。 

4. ADJ In English grammar, continuous verb groups are formed using the auxiliary 'be' and the present participle of a verb, as in 'I'm feeling a bit tired' and 'She had been watching them for some time.' Continuous verb groups are used especially when you are focusing on a particular moment. Compare . 进行 (时态) 的

